# Breezy Rhino Website Recreation - Walkthrough

## Summary of Changes
- **Project Structure**: Organized files into [index.html](file:///C:/Users/USER/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/breezy-rhino/index.html), [styles.css](file:///C:/Users/USER/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/breezy-rhino/styles.css), and [script.js](file:///C:/Users/USER/.gemini/antigravity/scratch/breezy-rhino/script.js) within `C:\Users\USER\.gemini\antigravity\scratch\breezy-rhino\`.
- **HTML Structure**: Created a semantic HTML5 structure with sections matching the original design (Hero, About, Services, Portfolio, Brands, Footer).
- **CSS Styling**: Implemented a dark theme (`#111` background), lime green accent colors (`#DFFF3B`), and bold typography using Google Fonts (Inter and Space Grotesk). Crafted a premium look using Flexbox/Grid layouts, large bold text, pill-shaped buttons and navigation, and 3D perspectives.
- **Interactions & Animations**: Integrated Lenis for smooth scrolling and GSAP ScrollTrigger for scroll-based animations:
  - Complex 3D parallax effects on the hero images when scrubbing the page.
  - Staggered fade-up and slide-up animations for text block and cards throughout all sections.
  - An image mask revealer on the About section.
  - An infinite CSS marquee for the Brands section.
  - A fixed, floating pill navigation bar with hover inversions.

## Validation Results
We used the browser subagent to navigate to the locally served website, scroll through it smoothly, and interact with the elements. We recorded the actions to confirm that the layout looks correct and that all GSAP animations trigger flawlessly.

